The paper proposes a new optimization algorithm based on swarm intelligence and echolocation behavior of bats. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also involves statistical tests to compare the performance of the proposed algorithm with other algorithms, indicating a focus on machine learning and data analysis, which suggests the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and search algorithms, which are relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The proposed algorithm also involves control and optimization of complex systems, which is relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimization of continuous functions, which is relevant to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category.
